<span id="freeTextContainer414956816357151751">This is not a review. I wrote something that aspired to be a review but fell short. In the end all you really need to know is that I loved it. I finished it standing in line at the grocery with tears running down my face because it was that beautiful. It’s the ruminations of a man at the end of his life, it’s confession, it’s revelation, it’s a parable in a parable. It’s hopeful. Read it.<br/><br/>I found this quote written on a scrap of something in my purse. <i>&quot;I know more than I know and must learn it fr</i></span>
  <span id="freeText414956816357151751" style="display:none">This is not a review. I wrote something that aspired to be a review but fell short. In the end all you really need to know is that I loved it. I finished it standing in line at the grocery with tears running down my face because it was that beautiful. It’s the ruminations of a man at the end of his life, it’s confession, it’s revelation, it’s a parable in a parable. It’s hopeful. Read it.<br /><br />I found this quote written on a scrap of something in my purse. <i>"I know more than I know and must learn it from myself."</i></span>
